name: Router
comment:
A simple nested router for single page applications.

See [Example](https://github.com/apuchenkin/elm-nested-router/tree/master/example) ([Live demo](http://apuchenkin.github.io/elm-nested-router/example))
and [Tests](https://github.com/apuchenkin/elm-nested-router/tree/master/test/Test) for more details

@docs dispatch, dispatchWithFlags, initialState

values.name: dispatch
values.comment:
Launches the router.
  Provide `init` function and router config as parameters
values.type: ( Router.Types.WithRouter route state , Platform.Cmd.Cmd (Router.Actions.Msg route msg) ) -> Router.Types.RouterConfig route (Router.Types.WithRouter route state) msg -> Platform.Program Basics.Never (Router.Types.WithRouter route state) (Router.Actions.Msg route msg)

values.name: dispatchWithFlags
values.comment:
Launches the router.
  Provide `init` function and router config as parameters
values.type: (flags -> ( Router.Types.WithRouter route state , Platform.Cmd.Cmd (Router.Actions.Msg route msg) )) -> Router.Types.RouterConfig route (Router.Types.WithRouter route state) msg -> Platform.Program flags (Router.Types.WithRouter route state) (Router.Actions.Msg route msg)

values.name: initialState
values.comment: Initial state for router. Fed this into your application state

name: Router.Types

aliases.name: GetConfig
aliases.comment: `Action` represents function that prforms something with application state, and might contain side efects

aliases.name: RouteConfig
aliases.comment:
A `Handler` is a piece of functionality binded to specific route
  * `render` — Function that describes how to render application state to map of named views
  * `actions` — A set of necessary to perform actions
aliases.type: { route : URL.Route.Config route , render : Router.Types.Render route state msg , actions : List msg }

aliases.name: Router
aliases.comment:
A `Router` is a provider of following functions:

  * `bindForward` — Binds a `forward` action to a provided `Route` with a list of html attributes.
    This is useful to create links in application
  * `buildUrl` — Builds an URL for provided `Route`
  * `forward` — Preforms a transition to provided `Route`
  * `redirect` — Redirects to provided `Route`
  * `match` — Performs attempt to match provided URL.

  Router also provide it's `config`
aliases.type: { config : Router.Types.RouterConfig route state msg , bindForward : URL.Route.Route route -> List (Html.Attribute (Router.Actions.Msg route msg)) -> List (Html.Attribute (Router.Actions.Msg route msg)) , buildUrl : URL.Route.Route route -> URL.Matcher.URL , forward : URL.Route.Route route -> Platform.Cmd.Cmd (Router.Actions.Msg route msg) , redirect : URL.Route.Route route -> Platform.Cmd.Cmd (Router.Actions.Msg route msg) }

aliases.name: WithRouter
aliases.comment: Type extension for the application state

types.name: RouterConfig
types.comment:
`RouterConfig` is configuration for the router:

  * `html5` — Use html5 pushState.
  * `removeTrailingSlash` — Trailing slashes will be removed from matched and builded urls
  * `layout` — Main rendered function that combines named views gathered from Handlers in a single HTML
  * `transition` — An action that should be executed on every router transition
  * `routeConfig` — A mapping between route and route configuration
  * `routes` — A list of routes available for routing
  * `subscriptions` — A list of subscriptions (see: [elm-lang/html](http://package.elm-lang.org/packages/elm-lang/html/1.1.0/Html-App) for details)
cases: { html5 : Bool , removeTrailingSlash : Bool , update : msg -> state -> ( state, Platform.Cmd.Cmd msg ) , layout : Router.Types.Router route state msg -> state -> Router.Types.Views route msg -> Html.Html (Router.Actions.Msg route msg) , onTransition : Router.Types.Router route state msg -> Router.Types.Transition route msg , routeConfig : Router.Types.GetConfig route state msg , routes : List route , subscriptions : state -> Platform.Sub.Sub (Router.Actions.Msg route msg) }
